Class instructionCases

java.lang.Object
  instructionCases

public class instructionCases
extends java.lang.Object

This class will have static methods for executing all the instructions. In addition, it will also contain private static methods for certain operations that are repeated within instructions.

Author:
GerardLouis

ADD

public static java.lang.String ADD(java.util.Map<java.lang.Integer,java.lang.String> registerMap,
                                   java.util.Map<java.lang.Character,java.lang.Boolean> conditionCodeRegisters,
                                   java.lang.String binaryRep,
                                   java.lang.Integer[] registerChanges)
This private method takes the string binaryRep that is passed in (it should contain 12 characters), and then does the ADD operation as outlined by "Wi-11 Machine Characteristics Document".

Parameters:
registerMap - This represents the general purpose registers that are available to the machine. There are 8 available, accessed by integers 0 through 7 and an error message will be returned if the user tries to access a register that is not there
conditionCodeRegisters - This represents the condition code registers, N, Z, and P. Depending on what the value of the number calculated, the corresponding register will get set or cleared (N for negative numbers, Z for zero values, and P for positive numbers)
binaryRep - This string of 12 characters should consist of '1's and '0's and each.
registerChanges - This array will be written to with the register number that was modified.
Returns:
A blank string or if errors are encountered, a string explaining the nature of the error.
